hat is the point of having these events on Meetup if we are scheduling 1-on-1 calls with another calendar?\n\n* These events were held in-person with 20 - 50 people attending once per month. Since the pandemic forced these events to move online, we have helped more people than we did in the past with in-person events. For this reason, the WordPress Help Desk events will remain online using scheduled 1-on-1 calls. Use the link above to schedule your call for a convenient time.',1,'Raleigh-Durham RTP WordPress Meetup Group','https://www.meetup.com/Raleigh-WordPress-Meetup-Group/','2024-01-04 09:00:00','-18000','2024-01-04 10:00:00','online','US',35.89,-78.64),(73349004,'meetup','297420663','scheduled','How to Write Accessible Website Copy: Abby Wood','https://www.meetup.com/wordpress-accessibility-meetup-group/events/297420663','A website\'s copy is often the first user interaction with a brand. In this talk, Abby will cover what good copywriting is and how to write it. We\'ll be taking a look at how to make your website copy accessible from various perspectives, including reading levels, neurodivergent needs, dyslexia, and Parkinson\'s. We\'ll cover how we train in-house copywriters to write accessible copy.\n\n**Thanks to our sponsors:**\n\n* [IvyCat](https://ivycat.com/website-accessibility/?utm_source=meetup&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=wpa11y_sponsor)\n* [Equalize Digital Accessibility Checker](https://equalizedigital.com/accessibility-checker/?utm_source=meetup&utm_medium=event-description)\n\n**Event Details:**\nThis meetup will be held at U.S. 8 AM Pacific, which is 10 AM U.S. Central, 4 PM in the UK, and 8:30 PM IST.\n\nRSVP to receive the link.\n\n**Accessibility & Accommodations:**\nThis meetup will be held virtually over Zoom and live captioned.\n\nSlide links will be provided when applicable, and presenters are encouraged to make slides as accessible as possible with alternative text for images, etc.\n\nWe\'re working to secure sponsors so that we can